fields.name: Scottish Shortbread
fields.instructions:
1.Cream the 200grams Butter and 100grams Sugar together until smooth
2. In a separate bowl sift 200 grams Plain flour and 100grams Rice flour together
3. Add the flour to the creamed butter and sugar and mix until the mixture appears crumbly
4. Turn the dough out onto a board and knead for 5 to 10 minutes till soft
5. Put the mixture into a 26cm x 16cm tin, pushing dough to the corners then smooth using a wooden spoon or small rolling pin
6. Cut the dough into chunky pieces or fingers, optional sprinkle with caster sugar
7. Use a fork to pierce the dough
8. Put in an oven, preheated to 180C. Bake for about 30 minutes. for a lovely light golden brown colour
9. Recut the shortbread in the tin while hot then let the shortbread cool in the tin.

fields.name: Meat Rissoles
fields.ingredients: Minced Meat, Breadcrumbs, Egg, Garlic, Onion, Parsley or Chives
fields.instructions:
1. Combine 300grams of minced Meat, 1 Egg, 1 Cup of Breadcrumbs, 1 Garlic clove chopped, 1 medium sized Onion chopped, some Parsley or Chives
2. Shape into balls, about 4-5cm in diameter, then flatten
3. Heat the pan, melt Ghee or heat oil then add the rissoles 3-4 at a time, depending on the pan size
4. Cook for about 5 to 8 minutes on each side

fields.name: Sponge Cake
fields.ingredients: Eggs, Sugar, Flour, Water, some Butter
fields.instructions:
1. Beat 2 egg whites, 90grams sugar and 1 tablespoon of water until soft peaks form, set aside
2. Beat 2 egg yolks and 90 grams of the sugar until smooth, then gently fold in the egg whites
3. Shift the Flour twice then slowly add it to the eggs mixture, gently mixing together
4 .Butter the inside of the cake tin and then roll some flour round the tin until every part is covered
5. Bake in a 180C fan-forced Oven for 25-30 minute, until Golden
6. ! IMPORTANT - DO NOT OPEN OVEN DURING THE FIRST 15-20 MINUTES!
7. After 25 minutes Test with a skewer that it is thoroughly baked.
8. Remove from oven and rest for 10 minutes on wire stand
9. Remove from cake tin

fields.name: Banana Yoghurt Smoothie
fields.instructions:
1. Add 1 Banana, really ripe Banana is best, and 100grams Yoghurt to a Blender
2. Blend until smooth, add some milk if too thick
3. optional add Honey to taste

fields.name: Swabian Potato Salad
fields.ingredients: Potatoes, Water, Vegetable Stock Cube, Vinegar, Oil, Onion and Chives(optional)
fields.instructions:
1. Boil the 10 medium sized Potatoes, in their skins, until soft
2. Remove the skin and let cool
3. Add 50ml boiling water to the Stock Cube until dissolved, add some Nutmeg
4. Add to the 2 Tablespoon of Apple Vinegar and 1 finely chopped Onion
5. Thinly slice the Potatoes into the liquid Vinegar mixture>br /> 6. Add 2 Tablespoons of Oil, any cold pressed is good
7. Rest for 30 -60 minutes, mix every 20 minutes

fields.name: Masala Chai or Spiced Tea
fields.ingredients: Water, Leaf Tea, Milk, Masala Spices(Chai)
fields.instructions:
1. Boil Water
2. Add it to Leaf Tea and Masala Spices
3. Let steep for 5 -6 minutes
4. Add milk to taste

fields.name: Chickpea and Almond Slice or Balls
fields.ingredients: tin chickpeas, almond butter, maple/golden syrup/honey, vanilla paste, baking powder, sea salt, dark choc chips or cacao nibs optional
fields.instructions:
1. Pre heat the oven to 180 C
2. Strain the tin of Chickpeas and put them into a food processor and pulse
3. Blend all the remaining ingredients (except the choc chips) until smooth and sticky
4. Mix in Choc chips or Cacao nibs
5. Either pour mixture into a small, lined baking tin or rolled into balls on tray
6. Bake for between 15 to 20 minutes
7. Allow to completely cool before cutting into portions

fields.name: Rum Balls
fields.ingredients: Crumbed Bisuits, Butter, Icing Sugar, Shredded Coconut, Rum
fields.instructions:
1. Crush one packet of unsweetened biscuits into very fine crumbs, similar to breadcrumbs
2. Whip the 50 grams of butter & 15 grams of icing sugar together
3. Slowly stir in biscuit crumbles and 30ml rum until stiff
4. Roll into balls and then roll into some coconut
5. Store in refrigerator

fields.name: Blue Cheese and Polenta Muffins
fields.ingredients: Polenta, Blue Cheese, Eggs, Milk, Water, Parmesan
fields.instructions:
1. Preheat Oven 200C
2. Mix 1 cup of Milk and 1 cup of Water in saucepan and bring to the boil
3. Add Salt and Pepper to taste and slowly stir in 3/4 cup of fine Polenta
4. Continue to stir in 1 direction until Polenta thickens, remove from heat
5. Whisk 2 Egg whites until stiff peaks form and set aside
6. Combine all other ingredients. EXCEPT the egg whites
7. Gentle fold in the egg whites to the mixture
8. Spoon the mix into Muffin Trays
9. Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until golden, and let cool in tins

fields.name: Polenta bake with Mushrooms
fields.ingredients: Sliced or Chopped Mushrooms, Chopped Parsley, Polenta, Butter, Olive Oil, Cream, Pecorino, Parmesan, Milk, Water
fields.instructions:
1. Preheat Oven to 180C
2. Melt the Butter and some Oil in a pan then saute the Mushrooms and Parsley, let cool
3. Pour Water and Milk into Saucepan and heat, 4. Whisk and slowly add the polenta, stir in one direction, until it begins to thicken, about 10 -15 mins
5. Mix the Cream, Pecorino and Parmesan and set aside
6. Pour half of Polenta into a Baking dish, add half of Mushroom mix, then half of cream mix, then layer rest of the Polenta, Mushroom and Cream
7. Sprinkle some Polenta and Parmesan on top
8. Bake for 15-20 minutes until Golden on top
9. Remove from Oven and let stand for 5 minutes, then serve.

fields.name: Scones plain
fields.ingredients: Self Rasing Flour, Egg, Milk, Butter, Icing Sugar
fields.instructions:
1. Preheat Oven to +250C
2. Mix 1 Cup of Self-Raising Flour, 1 Cup of Milk, 1 teaspoon of Butter, 1 teaspoon of Icing Sugar and 1 Egg together until combined, should have Molasses like consistency, add more Milk if required however DO NOT ADD EXTRA FLOUR
3. Pour mixture onto a floured board and flour top
4. Cut out scones and place onto a tray
5. Bake for 10mins or until golden, let cool
6. Place/wrap into a Tea Towel or Cloth until ready to serve.

fields.name: Chickpea and Black pepper Biscuits
fields.ingredients: Chickpea or Besan Flour, Black Sesame Seeds, Baking Powder, Freshly Ground Black Pepper, Salt, Olive Oil, Water
fields.instructions:
1. Pre-heat the Oven to 200C
2. Shift 1 Cup of Chickpea flour and 1 teaspoon of Baking powder together
3. Add the 2 tablespoons of Olive oil and 1 tablespoon of Water, to the Dry ingredients
4. If mix is too dry slowly add more water
5. Knead the dough by hand until smooth
6. Dust dough board with Chickpea flour and roll until about 1mm thick, occasionally flipping
7. Place onto Baking Paper or a Silicon sheet
8. Using a pastry cutter cut into either squares, rectangles or whatever shape you like
9. Sprinkle some course salt over the dough.
10. Bake in the Oven for 10-15 minutes or until golden.

fields.name: Cheese Ham and Mushroom Omelette
fields.ingredients: Eggs, Milk, Garlic, Grated Cheese, Ham, Mushrooms, Tomatoes, Chives or Parsley
fields.instructions:
1. Slice the 2 medium Tomatoes and 2 medium Mushrooms, finely chop 1 clove of Garlic and cut the Ham into strips
2. Melt Butter or Pan oil in a pan
3. Whisk 2 Eggs and 100ml Milk together
4. Pours mix into hot pan, then add all the other ingredients
5. Fry for about 5 mins, turn off the heat
6. Either flip 1 half over on top of the other or leave to until cooked
7. Remove from pan and sprinkle over with either finely chopped Chives or Parsley.

fields.name: Spiced Minced Meat and Vegetable Potato Top Pie
fields.ingredients: Potatoes, Butter, Milk , Minced Meat, Garlic, Carrots, Broccoli, Cauliflower, Mushrooms, Green Peas, Soya Sauce, Spices, Cheese
fields.instructions:
1. Preheat the Oven to 160-170C
2. Cook the 6-8 medium sized Potatoes until soft, then peel and mash with some nutmeg and either cream or milk with some butter
3. Slice 2 carrots and 6 medium mushrooms
4. Melt some butter or oil in a pan add the chopped garlic clove and 300grams of minced meat and any spice mix you like, (Indian, Mexican or Moroccan). Fry for 5-6 mins
5. Add the sliced carrots and mushrooms, the other Vegetable ingredients and some soya sauce stirring until lightly cooked
6. Pour the meat and vegetable mix into a baking dish, then pour the mashed potatoes to cover the meat mix entirely, level using a knife. Add the grated cheese on top of the mashed potatoes
7. Bake for 35-45 mins or until the cheese is melted and a crust has formed
8. Remove and leave stand for 5 mins, then serve.

fields.name: Anzac Biscuits
fields.ingredients: Self Raising Flour, Rolled Oats, Sugar, Shredded Coconut, Butter, Golden Syrup, Bicarb Soda, Water
fields.instructions:
1. Preheat Oven to 170C
2. Melt 125 grams Butter and 2 Tablespoons of Golden Syrup in a Saucepan
3. Combine 1 Cup of Self-Raising Flour, 1 Cup of Oatmeal, 3/4 Cup of Sugar and 3/4 Cup of Shredded Coconut
4. Add the 2 Tablespoons of boiling water to the 1 teaspoon of bicarb of soda. Stir, then quickly add to the melted butter and stir
5. Quickly add the dry ingredients to the foaming butter mix and combine
6. Using a dessertspoon, spoon mixture on to baking trays lined with silicon mats or baking paper
7. Bake for 15 minutes until baked then remove and leave to cool
8. Optional for hard biscuits turn off oven and leave for another 5-6 mins, becareful not to burn them

fields.name: Rusty Nail Cocktail
fields.instructions: 1. Add equal amounts Whisky and Drambuie into a mixing glass with ice.

fields.name: Lemon Poppy Seed Cake
fields.ingredients: Poppy Seeds, Self-Raising Flour, Butter, Sugar, Almond Meal, Milk, Eggs, Lemon Juice and Zest
fields.instructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 180C
2. Line 20 x 20 cm baking dish with baking paper
3. Beat the 115grams sugar and 115 grams softened butter until combined
4. Beat in 2 beaten eggs and the zest of 1/2 a Lemon
5. Mix in 100gram self-raising Flour, 80 grams almond meal, 80 grams poppy seeds and 4 Tablspoons od milk until combined
6. Pour mixture into the baking dish and bake for about 40 mins or until risen and golden brown on top
7. Mix the juice of 1 Lemon, 85grams sugar and the zest of 1/2 a Lemon. 8. Pour the Lemon Juice mix over the cake whilst hot and in baking dish.
9. Allow to cool in baking dish and when cool cut into squares.

fields.name: Lemon Poppy Seed Biscuits
fields.ingredients: Self-Raising Flour, Sugar, Poppy Seeds, Lemon, Butter, Honey, Egg, Vanilla Extract
fields.instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 175 degrees C fan-forced and line 2 baking trays with baking paper
á 2. In a small saucepan, bring 65ml of Lemon juice to a simmer, add 100g of the butter and let butter melt, remove from heat and set aside
3. Beat together, 150grams Butter, 2 Tablespoons of Honey and 150g of Sugar until smooth and creamy
4. Add 1 Egg and the melted lemon-butter mixture. Beat for 3 minutes, or until combined
5. Add 2 teaspoons of Vanilla Essences, zest of 1 Lemon and 4 Tablespoons of poppy seeds until combined
6. Add 420grams of sifter Self Raising Flour, mix until smooth. Then allow to stand for 10 minutes to firm
7. Combine remaining sugar with extra lemon zest on a large plate
8. Making walnut-sized balls of dough, roll them in the sugar and lemon zest mixture. Then place them on the lined trays, they will spread
9. Bake for 11-12 minutes, or until biscuits are golden around the edges. Set aside to cool on trays for 2 minutes before transferring biscuits to a wire rack to cool completely.
